	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dain belt is far better than Wormhusk for most melees. Stamina is nice, but its not hard to cap raid buffed. Group Boar adds +60 so you need 220-245 (depending if you have Planar Power max'd) to top off STA raid buffed. Stamina over 255 also yields diminished HP returns, so with shammy buff you only need 195 unbuffed STA before you start getting much smaller gains. 195-220 STA is not difficult to obtain for guilds at this level. My guild hasn't even scratched top-tier Ssra or Vex Thal yet and our rogues range from 180-240 STA unbuffed, its just not as tough as it used to be.<br><br>Now before Vex Thal, not counting a very tedious quest from Dozekar, there are only two innate AoB items attainable to most pure melees (this and Spirit Wracked Cords). 10 raw attack from AoB, which is 15 or 16 added to your ATK score with the modifier is awesome. Assuming everyone is at the haste cap besides what weapon you have ATK is what sets well geared rogues/monks apart from poorly geared ones. It makes a huge difference.<br><br>You can make arguments either way comparing a Wormhusk harness vs. a Belt of the Great Turtle for these classes, but its no match for Dain's belt.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
